The '''Viscera Film Festival''' was an annual [[Los Angeles]] based [[horror film]] festival for women filmmakers.<ref>Barone, Matt (May 30, 2013). "[http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2013/05/women-directors-horror-movies/viscera-film-festival The Unfair Business of Being of Woman Director in the Boys Club of Horror Filmmaking]." ''Complex''. Retrieved June 15, 2014.</ref> Originally an online festival, Viscera was founded in 2007 by [[Shannon Lark]] and Heidi Honeycutt.<ref>Sipos, Thomas M. (August 14, 2012). "[http://www.hollywoodinvestigator.com/2012/viscera2012.html Viscera Film Festival Honors Women Filmmakers]." ''Hollywood Investigator''. Retrieved June 15, 2014.</ref> In July 2010, the festival became a live event with screenings held at the [[Grauman's Egyptian Theatre|Egyptian Theatre]] in [[Hollywood]].<ref>Johnson, Kjerstin (July 14, 2010). "[http://bitchmagazine.org/post/women-in-horror-an-interview-with-the-directors-of-the-viscera-film-festival Scream Queens: An Interview with the founders of the Viscera Film Festival]". ''Bitch Magazine''. Retrieved June 15, 2014.</ref> All of the screenings were short films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://twitchfilm.com/2010/07/viscera-film-festival.html|title=Women of Horror Showcased at the Viscera Film Festival|last=Perkins|first=Rodney|work=[[Twitch Film]]|date=July 12, 2010|accessdate=July 21, 2014}}</ref> After the Egyptian Theatre premiere, Viscera toured their yearly film lineup at events held around the world for the rest of the year.<ref name=Marks>Marks, Lisa (July 12, 2012). "[https://www.theguardian.com/film/2012/jul/12/viscera-festival-los-angeles The horror, the horror: Women Gather in LA for Viscera Film Festival]". ''The Guardian''. Retrieved June 15, 2014.</ref> The Scream Queen Filmfest Tokyo was a subsidiary festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://twitchfilm.com/2013/09/scream-queen-filmfest-tokyo-a-two-day-celebration-of-female-horror-directors.html|title=Scream Queen Filmfest Tokyo: A Two-Day Celebration Of Female Horror Directors|last=Marsh|first=James|work=[[Twitch Film]]|date=September 15, 2013|accessdate=July 21, 2014}}</ref> == Inspiration Award == The Inspiration Award was founded in 2012 to honor women filmmakers.<ref name=Marks/> * 2012: [[Mary Lambert (director)|Mary Lambert]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bloody-disgusting.com/news/3149401/ca-readers-win-a-pair-of-tickets-to-the-viscera-film-festival-this-july/|title=CA Readers Win A Pair Of Tickets To The 'Viscera Film Festival' This July!|last=Miska|first=Brad|work=[[Bloody Disgusting]]|date=June 22, 2012|accessdate=July 21, 2014}}</ref> * 2013: [[Jennifer Lynch]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/jul/07/entertainment/la-et-mn-egyptian-viscera-horror-women-20130707|title=Viscera Film Festival: Horror movies and the women who direct them|last=King|first=Susan|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=July 7, 2013|accessdate=July 21, 2014}}</ref>
